\cf0 For the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/barbecue-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Barbecue sauce}}:\
Heat the oil in a medium {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} over medium heat.  Add the shallots and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/garlic/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 garlic}} and cook until soft, about 4 minutes.\
Add the wine, increase the heat to high and cook until reduced to about 1/2 cup. Add the ketchup and the remaining ingredients and cook until thickened and slightly reduced, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.  Transfer to a bowl and let cool slightly.\
For the salmon:\
Heat grill to high, cast iron {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill-pan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill pan}} over high heat, or large nonstick saute pan over high heat.  Brush {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salmon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 salmon}} on both sides with canola oil and season with salt and pepper.  Grill for about 4 minutes per side, brushing with some of the bbq sauce every 30 seconds.  Remove from the grill, place on a platter and brush with more of the sauce.  Garnish with parsley leaves and serve.\
